# Cloudflare Pages headers. Applied to every deployment (production + previews).
# CSP is deliberately last in the build (M11): a wrong CSP bricks the SPA.
# - script-src 'self' https://*.posthog.com : app JS is self-hosted (app.js, theme-init.js, analytics.js,
#                            vendor/*). No inline scripts (never 'unsafe-inline'). PostHog's library
#                            (array.full.js) loads from its EU assets host — hence the *.posthog.com allow
#                            (effort 0016; the owner chose the allow-list over a same-origin reverse proxy).
# - style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline' : inline style ATTRIBUTES are used (view-transition-name); esc() covers all
#                            dynamic content, so style injection is not a real vector. Dynamic bar widths use el.style (CSSOM).
# - img-src 'self' data: blob: : KV-served photos are same-origin; data: is the demo placeholder.
# - connect-src 'self' https://*.posthog.com : app fetch() hits /api/* and /data/*; PostHog sends events
#                            direct to eu.i.posthog.com (effort 0016). Map links are <a> navigations (not restricted here).
# NOTE: enabling PostHog Session Replay later also requires adding `worker-src 'self' blob:` (its
#       compression runs in a blob-URL Web Worker) — deliberately deferred; replay is off for now.
/*
  Content-Security-Policy: default-src 'self'; script-src 'self' https://*.posthog.com; style-src 'self' 'unsafe-inline'; img-src 'self' data: blob:; font-src 'self'; connect-src 'self' https://*.posthog.com; base-uri 'self'; form-action 'self'; frame-ancestors 'none'; object-src 'none'
  X-Content-Type-Options: nosniff
  Referrer-Policy: strict-origin-when-cross-origin
  X-Frame-Options: DENY
  Permissions-Policy: geolocation=(), camera=(), microphone=(), payment=(), usb=(), interest-cohort=()

/fonts/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/vendor/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable

/assets/*
  Cache-Control: public, max-age=31536000, immutable
